<article>

    <p><a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a></p>

    <h1>Pope al&#xAD;lows women more church roles</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <time datetime="2021-01-12"><a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210112/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-12">2021-01-12</a></time> -
        

            <a href="/category/tag-268487466/en/sg">Women&#x27;s Rights</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-268436537/en/sg">Religion</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-268485974/en/sg">Discrimination</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-268455461/en/sg">Christianity</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-268455460/en/sg">Catholic Church</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-268457475/en/sg">Human Rights</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-268436556/en/sg">Society</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-538110359/en/sg">Pope Francis</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-536891088/en/sg">Vatican</a>     </section>

        <p>• Pope Fran­cis, in an­other step towards greater equal­ity for women in the Ro­man Catholic Church, yes­ter­day changed its law to al­low them to serve as read­ers at litur­gies, al­tar servers and dis­trib­u­tors of com­mu­nion.</p>
        <p>In a de­cree, the Pope for­malised what has al­ready been hap­pen­ing in many coun­tries for years.</p>
        <p>But, with the change in the Code of Canon Law, con­ser­va­tive bish­ops will not be able to block women in their dio­cese from those roles.</p>
        <p>The Vat­i­can stressed, how­ever, that the roles were “es­sen­tially dis­tinct from the or­dained min­istry”, and were not an au­to­matic pre­cur­sor to women one day be­ing al­lowed to be or­dained priests.</p>
        <p>In the de­cree, called Spir­i­tus Do­mini, or The Spirit Of The Lord, Pope Fran­cis said he had acted af­ter the­o­log­i­cal re­flec­tion.</p>
        <p>In an ac­com­pa­ny­ing let­ter, the Pope said he wanted to bring “sta­bil­ity, pub­lic recog­ni­tion” to women al­ready serv­ing in the roles.</p>
        <p>REUTERS</p>


</article>

